SIMPLE: squish
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: squish
<hw>squish</hw> <pr>(skw⟦icr⟧sh)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Perh.
imitative. Cf. <er>Squelch</er>.]</ety> <def>To make the sound of
squirting water, like that made by the feet of one walking in mud or
slush; to make a kind of gushing, swashing, or splashing sound; to move
with such a sound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>squish</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: squish
<hw>squish</hw> <pr>(skw⟦icr⟧sh)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A sound like
that made by the feet of one walking in mud or slush; a gushing,
swashing, or splashing sound; a squishing sound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squitch grass</ent>⟦br⟧
